3-Day Cultural Trip to Rome

📅 Jul 2 – Jul 5 • 🧍 Solo traveler
Museums Cafes Solo Trip
{/* Trip Overview */}
Trip Overview

Immerse yourself in a cultural journey through Rome for 3 days. Visit renowned museums, wander historic districts, and relax in cozy Roman cafes. Highlights include a Vatican tour, the Colosseum, and a hands-on pasta-making class.

{/* Itinerary Summary + Map + Days */}
Itinerary

Rome is a city of deep history and culture, where you can visit iconic landmarks like the Colosseum, Roman Forum, and Pantheon. In 3 days, you'll soak up the Eternal City's atmosphere, stroll scenic alleys, and enjoy gelato near Trevi Fountain.

Day 1: Arrival in Rome Arrival, hotel check-in, and evening walk in the historic center. Day 2: Ancient Rome & Colosseum Explore the Colosseum, Roman Forum, and enjoy a traditional Roman dinner. Day 3: Vatican & Culinary Experience Morning visit to the Vatican Museums and St. Peter’s Basilica, followed by a pasta class. Day 4: Departure Breakfast and check-out. Optional morning walk or souvenir shopping. {/* Transfer Section */}
